<H1>About</H1>

<P><I><B>flPhoto</B></I> is a basic image management and display
program based on the <A HREF="http://www.fltk.org">FLTK</A>
toolkit and is provided under the terms of the <A
HREF="license.html">GNU General Public License</A>. It can read,
write, and display digital camera EXIF information and supports
the following image file formats:

<UL>

	<LI>AVI (first frame only)

	<LI>BMP

	<LI>JPEG

	<LI>PhotoCD

	<LI>PNG

	<LI>Various camera RAW formats
</UL>

<P><I><B>flPhoto</B></I> organizes image files into <A
HREF="albums.html">albums</A> which can be:

<UL>

	<LI><A HREF="print.html">Printed</A>

	<LI>Viewed as a <A HREF="slideshow.html">slideshow</A>

	<LI><A HREF="export.html">Exported</A> to web pages

</UL>

<P>Images can be <A HREF="import.html">imported</A>
individually, by directory, or from digital cameras using the <A
HREF="http://www.gphoto.org">gPhoto</A> library.

<P>Image files can be transformed and touched-up; the following
image operations are available:

<UL>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#CROP">Crop</A>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#ROTATE">Rotate</A>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#SCALE">Scale</A>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#AUTO">Auto-Correct</A>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#BRIGHTNESS">Adjust Brightness and Contrast</A>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#REDEYE">Remove Red Eye </A>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#SHARPEN">Sharpen</A>

	<LI><A HREF="images.html#BLUR">Blur</A>

</UL>

<P>Questions about <I><B>flPhoto</B></I> should be directed to
flphoto <I>at</I> easysw <I>dot</I> com or the <A
HREF="http://www.fltk.org/newsgroups.php">FLTK mailing lists and
newsgroups</A>.

